le J, et al.  Characterization of fusion determinants points to the involvement of three discrete regions of both E1 and E2 glycoproteins in the membrane fusion process of hepatitis C virus. <span><span class="ref-journal">J Virol. </span>2007;<span class="ref-vol">81</span>:8752\xe2\x80\x938765.</span> <span class="nowrap">[<a class="int-reflink" href="/pmc/articles/PMC1951381/">PMC free article</a>]</span> [<a href="/pubmed/17537855" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2824758&amp;issue-id=184533&amp;journal-id=349&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=J+Virol&amp;title=Characterization+of+fusion+determinants+points+to+the+involvement+of+three+discrete+regions+of+both+E1+and+E2+glycoproteins+in+the+membrane+fusion+process+of+hepatitis+C+virus.&amp;author=D+Lavillette&amp;author=EI+Pecheur&amp;author=P+Donot&amp;author=J+Fresquet&amp;author=J+Molle&amp;volume=81&amp;publication_year=2007&amp;pages=8752-8765&amp;pmid=17537855&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2824758&amp;issue-id=184533&amp;journal-id=349&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></div><div class="ref-cit-blk half_rhythm" id="ppat.1000762-Garry1">30. <span class="element-citation">Garry RF, Dash S. Proteomics computational analyses suggest that hepatitis C virus E1 and pestivirus E2 envelope glycoproteins are truncated class II fusion proteins. <span><span class="ref-journal">Virology. </span>2003;<span class="ref-vol">307</span>:255\xe2\x80\x93265.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/12667795" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2824758&amp;issue-id=184533&amp;journal-id=349&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Virology&amp;title=Proteomics+comput